Hmmm, yes, yes, like drying clothes. But the storm is
getting violent out there--it was angry to begin with, but
its temper has only gotten worse. It'll surely blow the
papers away. And anyhoo, I'm afraid to step an inch outside.

containment, everything should be fine!

div.span:
Oh, don't worry sir, the prongs already arrived. The red-hot
stack of top secret historic documents is sitting on my
desk. But sir, it's hard to flip through a stack of
documents with a pair of steel prongs.

div.span:
Yes, yes, don't puff me up too much. Anyway, there must be a
better solution than blowing--who has enough air in their
lungs for that?

I'm just glad I have this desk to hide behind! I assume
everything has gone according to plan for you, sir?

Oh, thank goodness, because that would be TERRIBLE. Anyways,
I have news about those documents containing all the events
in the history of Earth, including your mysterious death.

div.span:
You know I was a collector of many things on Earth. Well,
did you know I used to keep a PRISTINE collection of bowls
of creamy potato soup that hadn't been finished?

at once, you'll understand. You've just got to have them
all!

to your room soon enough. Everything is under control, Mr.
[playerLastName].

div.span:
Ah, sir, but we have to find out what killed you! We've come
so far, how can we stop now?

rect.style: fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px;

g.style: border-block-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-inline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); caret-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(204, 204, 204); column-rule-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; outline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none solid rgb(204, 204, 204); text-emphasis-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-fill-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);

span.style: padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px;

div.span:
We lost communication once again due to the storm. It's
really beginning to shake my walls like an angry toddler, or
an old man with a hand full of dice.

g.style: border-block-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-inline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); caret-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(204, 204, 204); column-rule-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; outline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none solid rgb(204, 204, 204); text-emphasis-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-fill-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);

span.style: padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px;

div.span:
And here's another thing: the paper is glowing. And when I
tried to touch it, it burnt me. I had to hold my hand under
the sink!

span.style: padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px;

div.span:
Obviously, I need to cool it down. I thought I might try
plunging the stack of documents in a cold bucket of water,
but that might destroy the paper. What do I do?

g.style: border-block-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-inline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); caret-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(204, 204, 204); column-rule-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; outline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none solid rgb(204, 204, 204); text-emphasis-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-fill-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);

span.style: padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px;

div.span:
Hmmm, yes, yes, like cooling a bowl of creamy potato. But
that might take a little while, don't you think?

rect.style: fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px;

g.style: border-block-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-inline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); caret-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(204, 204, 204); column-rule-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; outline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none solid rgb(204, 204, 204); text-emphasis-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-fill-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);

span.style: padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px;

div.span:
Yes, about fourty years ago I securely locked Shrimp in the
most safe and happy room imagineable. But a red light just
lit up at my desk notifying me that he had escaped. You
didn't happen to see a large, four-legged thing, did you?

rect.style: fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px;

g.style: border-block-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-inline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); caret-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(204, 204, 204); column-rule-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; outline-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none solid rgb(204, 204, 204); text-emphasis-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-fill-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); -webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(204, 204, 204);

span.style: padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px;

div.span: Well I think. Sir, there must be a better solution.

rect.style: fill: rgb(13, 0, 50); font-family: 'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 25.6px; padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px; stroke: rgb(42, 0, 168); stroke-width: 5px;

span.style: padding-block: 5px; padding: 5px; padding-inline: 5px;

div.span:
Well, there's a lot of documents. I mean there's so much
paper it had to be creased and folded like origami just to
fit in the box. It's like a dense cube of paper.

Well, as long as you didn't release Shrimp from his
containment, everything should be fine!
